# Nicos Reflective Product Philosophy

Nicos is a private container for year-long self-cultivation, not a productivity tool.

## Experience Principles

- Prioritize stillness over density: prefer fewer blocks with generous whitespace.
- Treat pages as places to return to, not tasks to complete.
- Preserve time-awareness (week, month, year) without turning it into performance tracking.
- Keep transitions and interaction gentle; avoid pushy prompts and noisy feedback.

## Avoid

- SaaS dashboard patterns, KPI-heavy summaries, completion pressure.
- Habit tracker/game mechanics, streak language, optimization framing.
- Notion-clone visuals (dense control surfaces, utilitarian data-grid feel by default).

## Copy Tone

- Warm, restrained, intimate, clear.
- Prefer language patterns: notice, return, revisit, what surfaced, what stayed, what shifted, carry forward.
- Avoid: optimize, boost productivity, achieve more, fix yourself, become your best self.

## UI Guidance

- Use calm hierarchy and editorial composition.
- Keep cards soft and minimal; avoid decorative overload.
- Let unfinished entries and fragments feel valid and held.
